Confirmation prompt at startup.description: Prompt me to confirm starting of the script because it will overwrite the current active drawing. You can disable this warning by turning off this switch

Max number of nodes/domain.description: Maximum number of items to show in each domain: parents, children, siblings, jumps.

Infer non-Breadcrumbs links.description: Links on the page are children, backlinks to the page are parents. Breadcrumbs take priority.

Hide attachments.description: Hide attachments. Will only have an effect if Infer non-Breadcrumbs links is turned on.

Central font size.description: Font size of the central node

Font size.description: Font size of jumps, children and parents

Max label length.description: Maximum number of characters to display from node title. Longer nodes will end with '...'

Gate offset.description: The offset to the left and right of the parent and child gates.

Gate radius.description: The radius of the 3 small circles (alias: gates) serving as connection points for nodes

Canvas color.description: Any legal HTML color (#000000, rgb, color-name, etc.).

Gate color.description: Any legal HTML color (#000000, rgb, color-name, etc.).

Link color.description: Any legal HTML color (#000000, rgb, color-name, etc.).

Central-node background color.description: Any legal HTML color (#000000, rgb, color-name, etc.).

Central-node color.description: Any legal HTML color (#000000, rgb, color-name, etc.).

Breadcrumbs-node background color.description: Any legal HTML color (#000000, rgb, color-name, etc.).

Breadcrumbs-node color.description: Any legal HTML color (#000000, rgb, color-name, etc.).

Non-breadcrumbs-node background color.description: Any legal HTML color (#000000, rgb, color-name, etc.).

Non-breadcrumbs-node color.description: Any legal HTML color (#000000, rgb, color-name, etc.).

Virtual-node background color.description: Any legal HTML color (#000000, rgb, color-name, etc.).

Virtual-node color.description: Any legal HTML color (#000000, rgb, color-name, etc.).

Display alias if available.description: Displays the page alias instead of the filename if it is specified in the page's front matter.

Graph settings JSON.description:
This may contain two elements:
  1. A specification of your breadcrumbs hierarchy. Note, that if you have the Breadcrumbs plugin installed and enabled then TheBrain-navigation script will take your hierarchy settings from Breadcrumbs. If Breadcrumbs is disabled, this specification will be used.
  2. Formatting of nodes based on page tags. You can specify special formatting rules for tags. If multiple tags are present on the page the first matching a specification will be used. You may provide partial specifications as well. e.g. if you only specify prefix, the other attributes will follow your default settings.
{
  "breadcrumbs": {
    "down": ["children", "child"],
    "up": ["parents", "parent"],
    "jump": ["jump", "jumps"]
  },
  "tags": {
    "#excalidraw": {
      "nodeColor": "hsl(59, 80%, 77%)",
      "gateColor": "#fd7e14",
      "borderColor": "black",
      "backgroundColor": "rgba(50,50,50,0.5)",
      "prefix": "üé® "
    },
    "#dnp": {
      "prefix": "üóì "
    }
  }
}
